  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Methamphetamine substance use is common worldwide. No approved pharmacologic treatments for
      methamphetamine dependence exist. Aripiprazole are Second generation antipsychoticsï¼Œbut have
      different pharmacological effects of neurotransmitters.To determine whether mirtazapine would
      reduce methamphetamine use among mehtamphetamine addicts.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Methods:A Multiple-Center, Randomized, Double-Blind.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
  <overall_status>Terminated</overall_status>
  <why_stopped>
